  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key Preventive Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset freezing and seizure\n- Criminal prosecution of offenders\n\n4. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training on money laundering detection\n- Maintain detailed transaction records\n\n5. International Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint law enforcement efforts\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
